I&#39;m not sure if it&#39;s really related or not but this early in the morning it seems like it could be...

last night I saw a show on the science channel where a group of people were testing robots to see just how dumb they could be and still do something useful.

the bots were turned loose in an &quot;arena&quot; and they just wandered around pretty much aimlessly. 
when they come across a puck they grab it and continue to wander around until they hit something.
if what they hit is a wall they turn and continue.
if they hit another puck they do 1 of 2 things.
if the puck they have is white they drop the puck where they are.
if they have a black puck they move away from the other puck and drop it.
(I think those were the rules...)

anyway, after a while they had sorted all the pucks so that the white ones were clustered together.

They were not specifically trying to sort the pucks into a cluster but they did it anyway.

could they see the forest through all those trees :-)











